  "title": "axletree",
  "sourceFile": "Burbank_notes/axletree_N.htm",
  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>axletree</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>The axletree is the tree of which the\n        axis of Chariots used to be made and in classical times\n        the burning chariot driven by Phoebus was the sun. Eliot\n        refers to a similar image in Seneca's <em>Hercules Furens\n        </em>and Chapman's <em>Bussy D'Ambois</em>, two fragments\n        which he has on at least three different occasions\n        compared to each other. </font></p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"axletree.htm\">Eliot\n                and the axletree</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"axletree.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Istria_H.htm\">Istria\n                in Herod</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Istria_H.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sir Ferdinand Klein</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "axletree The axletree is the tree of which the axis of Chariots used to be made and in classical times the burning chariot driven by Phoebus was the sun. Eliot refers to a similar image in Seneca's Hercules Furens and Chapman's Bussy D'Ambois , two fragments which he has on at least three different occasions compared to each other. reference topics Eliot and the axletree Istria in Herod Sir Ferdinand Klein back to \"Burbank\"",
